WEBVTT

00:01.436 --> 00:03.351
- Previously
on "Resident Alien"...

00:03.394 --> 00:04.656
- How long do you think I have?

00:04.700 --> 00:06.789
- Do you like Christmas?
- Yes, very much.

00:06.832 --> 00:08.791
- Celebrate it before June.

00:08.834 --> 00:10.401
- My birthday's coming up.

00:10.445 --> 00:14.101
I was wondering if you might
want to do something that day.

00:14.144 --> 00:15.537
- I would love that.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.800
- Pick me up
at the diner at 1:00?

00:17.843 --> 00:18.975
- [squeals]

00:19.019 --> 00:20.672
- [screams]

00:20.716 --> 00:22.848
The baby hatched.

00:22.892 --> 00:25.025
- What the...?

00:25.068 --> 00:27.114
[alien baby hisses]
[both scream]

00:27.157 --> 00:29.072
- It's a stupid kiss.
Who cares?

00:29.116 --> 00:31.248
D'arcy was drunk and sad.
Big surprise.

00:31.292 --> 00:32.510
- Maybe you should learn
to talk to Ben

00:32.554 --> 00:33.685
about your feelings
instead of stuffing them

00:33.729 --> 00:35.035
inside a 90-mile vertical
treadmill run.

00:35.078 --> 00:36.340
- Hello, Harry.

00:36.384 --> 00:38.255
Our people are not coming
to kill everyone.

00:38.299 --> 00:39.691
There is an alien race
that's planning

00:39.735 --> 00:41.084
to take over the Earth.
They are--

00:41.128 --> 00:43.130
[gunshot]
- Whoa.

00:43.173 --> 00:45.262
- I should have never made you
kill Sam Hodges.

00:45.306 --> 00:47.134
- You shot me.

00:47.177 --> 00:49.701
- I should have just taken
care of it myself.

00:49.745 --> 00:51.355
[gunshot]

00:51.399 --> 00:53.749
- I just wanna forget
the whole thing.

00:53.792 --> 00:56.099
- I can erase
all of her memories

00:56.143 --> 01:00.277
of that night for her,
and she will be happy again.

01:00.321 --> 01:05.195
She will forget,
and everything will be okay.

01:07.502 --> 01:10.635
[suspenseful music]

01:10.679 --> 01:17.468
♪

01:17.512 --> 01:20.080
- I'm tired.
I wanna go home.

01:20.123 --> 01:21.559
- Shush now.

01:21.603 --> 01:24.171
Mama said not to come home
until we fetch some dinner.

01:34.833 --> 01:36.835
- Bobby! Wait for me.

01:36.879 --> 01:43.625
♪

01:55.854 --> 01:58.901
Bobby!

01:58.944 --> 02:01.251
Bobby, where are you?

02:05.125 --> 02:07.257
Bobby?
Bobby?

02:07.301 --> 02:09.172
- Bobby?
- Bobby!

02:09.216 --> 02:10.869
- Bobby?
- Where are you, Bobby?

02:10.913 --> 02:13.133
- Bobby!
- Bobby?

02:13.176 --> 02:16.136
[Brown Bird's "Bilgewater"]

02:16.179 --> 02:19.095
[laid-back acoustic strumming]

02:19.139 --> 02:23.491
♪

02:26.755 --> 02:29.410
[tranquil music]

02:29.453 --> 02:31.281
- Who is in my house?

02:31.325 --> 02:33.762
Max, if that is you
and your criminal wife,

02:33.805 --> 02:36.460
I will be very angry.

02:36.504 --> 02:40.160
- Good morning.
- You are not a little child.

02:40.203 --> 02:41.813
- I made coffee.

02:44.294 --> 02:46.818
Hey, I think we should check
on the alien egg.

02:46.862 --> 02:48.646
I'm a little worried
that the noise from the party

02:48.690 --> 02:50.996
might have woken it up
or something.

02:51.040 --> 02:53.956
- The memory replacement I did
on her worked well.

02:53.999 --> 02:57.394
She does not remember
that the alien baby escaped.

02:57.438 --> 02:59.396
She also forgot
how to make coffee.

02:59.440 --> 03:02.094
This tastes like dirt stew.

03:02.138 --> 03:04.445
Do not worry about the baby.

03:04.488 --> 03:07.665
It is in the bunker
in its shell

03:07.709 --> 03:10.320
and definitely not
somewhere else who-knows-where.

03:10.364 --> 03:12.670
- That's a relief.
[chuckles]

03:12.714 --> 03:15.934
I will take good news wherever
I can get it these days.

03:18.241 --> 03:20.243
- A smile?

03:20.287 --> 03:23.159
I like smiley Asta much more
than the sad, sobby Asta

03:23.203 --> 03:24.508
I saw last night.

03:24.552 --> 03:26.902
I have some more good news
for you to smile to.

03:26.945 --> 03:28.338
- Okay.

03:28.382 --> 03:32.821
- I was in the bunker
and definitely nowhere else,

03:32.864 --> 03:34.910
checking on the baby,

03:34.953 --> 03:37.956
and it gave me
a message telepathically.

03:38.000 --> 03:41.699
My people are no longer coming
to destroy mankind.

03:41.743 --> 03:45.877
- What?
How does it even know that?

03:45.921 --> 03:49.185
- Goliath passed the message
to me through the alien.

03:49.229 --> 03:52.188
I do not even know
how he did it.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.146
It was so weird.

03:54.190 --> 03:58.890
You no longer have to ever
make me feel uncomfortable

03:58.934 --> 04:00.414
with your sadness again.

04:01.763 --> 04:03.112
- They're really not coming?

04:03.155 --> 04:06.898
- Mm.
- You're serious?

04:06.942 --> 04:10.293
- No, I'm not serious.
I'm smiling.

04:10.337 --> 04:12.208
- [laughs]
Harry.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.862
Oh, Harry,

04:13.905 --> 04:15.733
this is the best news
I've ever heard in my life.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.953
[both laugh]

04:17.996 --> 04:20.390
Oh, wow. I'm so happy.

04:20.434 --> 04:24.046
Wait, wait.
Did it say anything else?

04:24.089 --> 04:27.441
- Yes, there is another
evil alien race on Earth

04:27.484 --> 04:29.965
that will probably
kill us all.

04:30.008 --> 04:33.925
No, it did not,
just the good stuff.

04:33.969 --> 04:35.318
Happy Asta.

04:35.362 --> 04:40.497
- Finally, after everything,
it's over?

04:42.107 --> 04:46.155
[sighs]
We're safe.

04:46.198 --> 04:48.592
- No, the Earth is doomed,
but at least

04:48.636 --> 04:52.553
I do not have to clean
crying snot off your face.

04:55.033 --> 04:58.863
I have completed
a full autopsy on the victim,

04:58.907 --> 05:01.170
Tanner Corrington.

05:01.213 --> 05:03.041
My initial theory
after you found

05:03.085 --> 05:04.608
the shell casing in the woods

05:04.652 --> 05:08.046
was that the crime
was committed with a rifle

05:08.090 --> 05:09.309
where the murderer

05:09.352 --> 05:11.441
was standing
over the county line

05:11.485 --> 05:13.182
in Patience.

05:13.225 --> 05:17.360
- Mm, wild speculation.
Continue.

05:17.404 --> 05:22.496
- The chest wound shows no sign
of soiling or tattooing

05:22.539 --> 05:26.064
proving that the gun
was fired mid to far range.

05:26.108 --> 05:27.805
My official findings

05:27.849 --> 05:31.809
are consistent
with my initial theory.

05:31.853 --> 05:36.161
I was right,
and now I'm more right.

05:36.205 --> 05:38.860
- Yeah, well, Patience shooter
means Patience murder.

05:38.903 --> 05:40.949
- Mm, objection.
- Overruled.

05:40.992 --> 05:42.820
- Sustained.
- It's not a trial.

05:42.864 --> 05:44.387
It's an autopsy.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.562
- Yes, but how
can we really know

05:45.606 --> 05:48.173
what happens
based on a dead body?

05:48.217 --> 05:49.523
- The autopsy.

05:49.566 --> 05:52.090
- That hole
could be from anything.

05:52.134 --> 05:54.397
Hey, you want close range?
I'll give you close range.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.356
A Jessup murderer
lights a firecracker,

05:56.399 --> 05:58.053
pressed it in the guy's chest.

05:58.096 --> 05:59.881
Bam, dead guy,
killer with three fingers.

05:59.924 --> 06:01.273
We are looking

06:01.317 --> 06:03.101
for a three-fingered
Jessup resident,

06:03.145 --> 06:05.190
maybe someone
who works at the gas station.

06:05.234 --> 06:06.627
I think piano teachers are out.

06:06.670 --> 06:09.673
So look into that.
Let me know what you find.

06:09.717 --> 06:12.807
- This man is more annoying
than his son.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.504
- This all seems
very thorough, Doctor.

06:14.548 --> 06:16.680
Thank you.

06:16.724 --> 06:18.639
Looks like
we're partners on this one.

06:21.381 --> 06:23.295
- I want this dead thing gone.

06:23.339 --> 06:24.558
Every time I look at it,

06:24.601 --> 06:25.950
I'm reminded
that if the bullet

06:25.994 --> 06:28.431
that hit me was
a few inches lower--

06:28.475 --> 06:30.433
[shrieks]

06:31.739 --> 06:34.394
- Why do you scream
like my mother?

06:36.613 --> 06:39.311
- It was not a scream.
It was a sneeze.

06:39.355 --> 06:40.617
Ha-ha-choo!

06:42.358 --> 06:44.142
I have a very thin larynx.

06:44.186 --> 06:45.666
- Here's your schedule.

06:45.709 --> 06:48.408
Also, Gerard Hundemer
needs you to do a house call

06:48.451 --> 06:49.670
to bring him pain medication.

06:49.713 --> 06:52.455
- He's dying.
I do not want to go.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.501
It is depressing. Cancel.

06:54.544 --> 06:56.285
- You're joking, right?

06:56.328 --> 06:58.026
- Of course I'm joking.
Ha-ha-ha.

06:58.069 --> 07:00.289
Reschedule it
till after he is dead.

07:00.332 --> 07:05.425
- Also, you need to sign this
to release the body.

07:08.253 --> 07:12.780
- I will be happy when this
annoying lump of skin is gone.

07:12.823 --> 07:14.434
- The funeral home
is shipping it back

07:14.477 --> 07:15.609
to New York this afternoon.

07:15.652 --> 07:18.481
- I was talking about you.
[chuckles]

07:19.961 --> 07:22.746
- I suggest you don't
leave food in the fridge.

07:22.790 --> 07:25.270
- No, you will leave
my yogurt alone.

07:25.314 --> 07:27.621
Oh, ew.

07:32.843 --> 07:35.846
- Hello.
- [screams]

07:35.890 --> 07:37.935
Choo.

07:37.979 --> 07:41.156
- Bless you?
- What are you doing in here?

07:41.199 --> 07:42.679
This is not your home.

07:42.723 --> 07:44.115
- Well, I was in the kitchen,

07:44.159 --> 07:46.640
but they're out
of those yogurts I like, so...

07:46.683 --> 07:50.208
- Those are my yogurts.
- Is Asta around?

07:50.252 --> 07:51.732
I haven't heard from her.

07:51.775 --> 07:54.822
- I forgot about Asta's
friendship with Raggedy Ann.

07:54.865 --> 07:57.477
I cannot have her remind Asta
she is a killer.

07:57.520 --> 07:59.087
Asta has the day off.

07:59.130 --> 08:03.526
If you see her,
do not mention...

08:03.570 --> 08:06.224
the "incident."
- What incident?

08:06.268 --> 08:08.749
I don't know
what you're talking about.

08:10.402 --> 08:11.578
- The murder.

08:11.621 --> 08:13.667
- I know what
you're talking about.

08:13.710 --> 08:15.451
- You said you did not know
what I was talking about.

08:15.495 --> 08:17.409
- Because I don't
wanna talk about it.

08:17.453 --> 08:18.541
- I do not want
to talk about it.

08:18.585 --> 08:19.890
I do not even care.

08:19.934 --> 08:22.937
- You're in denial.
- I am not in denial.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.635
- So you're in denial
about being in denial?

08:25.679 --> 08:29.987
- Yes. No.
I deny denying it.

08:30.031 --> 08:32.076
- Yeah, I just--

08:32.120 --> 08:34.688
what made somebody
wanna kill you,

08:34.731 --> 08:37.081
Harry Vanderspeigle?

08:37.125 --> 08:38.518
You say it's 'cause
you figured out

08:38.561 --> 08:41.608
who killed Sam Hodges.

08:41.651 --> 08:43.827
Are you sure
it's not something else?

08:43.871 --> 08:46.874
- Your breath smells like corn
and kerosene.

08:46.917 --> 08:51.531
- I would do anything for Asta,

08:51.574 --> 08:53.184
so if you've dragged her

08:53.228 --> 08:56.100
into something
that's gonna hurt her,

08:56.144 --> 08:59.713
I might just have
to kill you myself.

09:02.150 --> 09:03.194
You know what
I'm talking about?

09:03.238 --> 09:05.066
- [laughs]

09:05.109 --> 09:12.029
♪

09:13.640 --> 09:16.077
- Help. Help!

09:18.383 --> 09:21.909
I need help. Something bit me.

09:23.432 --> 09:24.999
- Ellen, I need a large bandage

09:25.042 --> 09:27.392
and those three yogurts
you stole.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.090
- You have no proof.

09:31.092 --> 09:33.050
- What did this?

09:34.791 --> 09:36.532
- They'll say I'm crazy,

09:36.576 --> 09:39.709
but I think
it was a chupacabra.

09:39.753 --> 09:42.538
A tiny monster.
It attacked my cows.

09:42.582 --> 09:44.366
- It ate them?

09:44.409 --> 09:47.674
- No. It milked them.

09:47.717 --> 09:49.589
12 of my poor girls
have damaged teats.

09:49.632 --> 09:51.068
What am I gonna do?

09:51.112 --> 09:53.723
I have 35 dairy cows
filled with milk.

09:53.767 --> 09:56.291
- Yum.
- What?

09:56.334 --> 09:58.162
- What?

09:58.206 --> 09:59.990
With that many
milk sacks to drain,

10:00.034 --> 10:02.297
the alien baby
will go back for more.

10:02.340 --> 10:03.733
- Here it is.

10:03.777 --> 10:06.736
- Ellen, please bandage
the milk farmer.

10:06.780 --> 10:09.043
I have an emergency.

10:14.048 --> 10:17.355
[soft music]

10:17.399 --> 10:24.319
♪

10:29.716 --> 10:33.589
- Hey.
- Hi.

10:33.633 --> 10:38.246
- Great party the other night.
Wait, were you there?

10:40.727 --> 10:42.293
- I'm sorry I said what I said.

10:42.337 --> 10:44.687
- Don't be.
It's all true.

10:44.731 --> 10:47.777
What I did...sucked.

10:47.821 --> 10:50.301
I was truly an asshole.

10:50.345 --> 10:53.217
- Look, Ben and I have things
to work out, obviously,

10:53.261 --> 10:55.567
and, you know,
if he can't talk to me,

10:55.611 --> 10:57.352
then he and I
will deal with that,

10:57.395 --> 11:01.443
but I just wish
he would've told me.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.229
- I should have.

11:06.448 --> 11:08.755
I--you have every right
to be pissed.

11:08.798 --> 11:10.321
- I've lived here a long time,

11:10.365 --> 11:14.543
and I still--I still
don't really know anybody.

11:14.586 --> 11:17.459
So when you and I started
hanging out, it was nice...

11:19.200 --> 11:21.550
Not feeling so alone.

11:23.944 --> 11:26.337
- It's nice having someone else
here with athletic trophies

11:26.381 --> 11:27.774
gathering dust on a shelf.

11:27.817 --> 11:29.689
- Mine are in a box, but--

11:29.732 --> 11:33.257
♪

11:33.301 --> 11:35.695
Need someone to spot you?

11:35.738 --> 11:38.001
- Need someone make fun of you
when you run?

11:38.045 --> 11:39.873
- Weirdly,
that's exactly what I need.

11:39.916 --> 11:40.917
- [laughs]

11:40.961 --> 11:42.527
[cow moos]

11:42.571 --> 11:43.877
- I love cows.

11:43.920 --> 11:46.270
Humans could live
on a plant-only diet,

11:46.314 --> 11:47.968
but they are too selfish.

11:48.011 --> 11:50.318
They choose to feed
off these wonderful animals

11:50.361 --> 11:52.886
instead of just letting them
live their lives.

11:52.929 --> 11:55.627
[cows mooing]

11:55.671 --> 11:57.194
[chirruping]

11:57.238 --> 11:59.327
I must wait here
as long as it takes

11:59.370 --> 12:01.459
for the baby
to return and feed.

12:01.503 --> 12:03.766
Otherwise,
it may take human form,

12:03.810 --> 12:06.464
and I may never find it.

12:08.945 --> 12:13.254
- Get outta here!
Go on, go on!

12:13.297 --> 12:18.041
I'm gonna teach you a lesson,
you nasty, little devil.

12:18.085 --> 12:20.740
You leave my cows alone.
You hear me?

12:20.783 --> 12:23.743
[quirky music]

12:23.786 --> 12:26.223
♪

12:26.267 --> 12:29.052
- [applauds]
I've got good news.

12:29.096 --> 12:31.663
- The only news I want to hear
is that you gonna stop clapping

12:31.707 --> 12:34.971
your bony, porcelain hands
before they trigger a migraine.

12:35.015 --> 12:37.147
- Just regular hands.

12:37.191 --> 12:40.194
Uh, so the resort company

12:40.237 --> 12:42.370
has officially put an offer
on the Grady land.

12:42.413 --> 12:44.981
It's great news
for you and your department.

12:45.025 --> 12:47.897
You know, more tourism money
means you can hire more people,

12:47.941 --> 12:49.029
you know, more equipment.

12:49.072 --> 12:51.683
- Hmm, and why do I think

12:51.727 --> 12:54.991
there's a "the only thing is"
attached to this?

12:55.035 --> 12:57.167
- I'm just giving you
the good news.

12:57.211 --> 12:58.516
You know, the only th--

13:01.128 --> 13:05.349
There is one factor
to consider.

13:05.393 --> 13:09.223
If the resort people hear
that Patience is involved

13:09.266 --> 13:11.747
in another murder,
they may go somewhere else.

13:11.791 --> 13:14.532
- [sighs]
I see.

13:14.576 --> 13:17.709
- So I was thinking maybe
you could take a back seat

13:17.753 --> 13:19.711
and let Jessup take the reins
on this investigation.

13:19.755 --> 13:21.670
- When have you ever seen me
take a backseat?

13:21.713 --> 13:23.367
I don't even sit
in the backseat of a car.

13:23.411 --> 13:26.457
If I hail a cab,
I sit shotgun, or I drive.

13:28.068 --> 13:30.418
- Look, just...
[sighs]

13:30.461 --> 13:32.855
Just think about it, please.

13:32.899 --> 13:36.772
Look, I--I need this.

13:36.816 --> 13:39.601
I need something to go right.
- Ah.

13:39.644 --> 13:43.735
So now we're getting around
to what this is really about.

13:43.779 --> 13:46.869
So you're having some trouble
at home?

13:46.913 --> 13:48.349
- What? No.

13:48.392 --> 13:50.307
Everything's--
everything's fine.

13:50.351 --> 13:51.831
- You know I'm
the town sheriff, right?

13:51.874 --> 13:55.486
Which means 100% of my job
is being a therapist.

13:55.530 --> 13:57.619
- That percentage seems high.

13:57.662 --> 14:01.188
- It's not.
If anything, it's low.

14:01.231 --> 14:04.800
Look, I went through
some things a while back

14:04.844 --> 14:07.759
that I didn't deal with,

14:07.803 --> 14:11.502
and sometimes
you gotta face life head on.

14:11.546 --> 14:13.896
You know, you can't run away
from your problems.

14:13.940 --> 14:16.681
They come back,
and they'll eat you alive.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.988
You understand?

14:19.032 --> 14:21.773
- Yeah. I know that.

14:21.817 --> 14:22.818
I--

14:22.862 --> 14:24.559
[soft music]

14:24.602 --> 14:28.041
It's just hard
to talk to her sometimes.

14:28.084 --> 14:29.259
- Well, I get it.

14:29.303 --> 14:30.782
When it comes
to talking to 'em,

14:30.826 --> 14:33.524
you gotta treat women
like they in the cartel, right?

14:33.568 --> 14:36.179
You wanna have a conversation?
You take 'em to a public place.

14:36.223 --> 14:38.355
That way you don't have to
worry about them murdering you.

14:38.399 --> 14:40.836
- So you think Kate
wants to murder me?

14:40.880 --> 14:42.751
- Based on the fight
at the party,

14:42.794 --> 14:44.796
I put the odds at, like,

14:44.840 --> 14:47.190
I don't know, 35%.

14:47.234 --> 14:48.800
- Seems high.

14:48.844 --> 14:50.237
- You got life insurance?

14:50.280 --> 14:52.892
'Cause that'll push it up
to, like, 60.

14:52.935 --> 14:55.851
[alien baby chittering]

15:00.943 --> 15:04.077
[eerie music]

15:04.120 --> 15:07.167
[voices echoing indistinctly]

15:10.997 --> 15:13.521
[people shouting]

15:13.564 --> 15:15.305
- What is happening
to my body?

15:15.349 --> 15:17.829
My mouth is dry.
I cannot breathe.

15:17.873 --> 15:21.964
My heart feels
like it will explode.

15:22.008 --> 15:25.489
This is fear of death.

15:25.533 --> 15:27.970
I am not ready to die.

15:28.014 --> 15:30.842
[voices shouting]

15:30.886 --> 15:33.497
♪

15:35.499 --> 15:37.937
- ♪ I woke up
on the wrong side ♪

15:37.980 --> 15:40.243
♪ Of the law

15:40.287 --> 15:42.550
[acoustic blues music]

15:42.593 --> 15:45.292
- Yo, stinky,
can I get two more?

15:45.335 --> 15:47.685
- Hey, speed it up
on those beers, skank.

15:47.729 --> 15:51.341
- My God.
Brenda is so annoying.

15:51.385 --> 15:53.387
She, like,
follows me everywhere.

15:53.430 --> 15:56.042
- I really cannot imagine
what that feels like.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.739
- Oh, well, it feels like

15:57.782 --> 15:59.567
she's obsessed with me,
you know?

15:59.610 --> 16:01.482
And she's not like--
you know, like us.

16:01.525 --> 16:04.137
- Whoo-hoo, yeah!

16:04.180 --> 16:07.967
- Yeah, we get it, Brenda.
You're playing pool.

16:10.708 --> 16:12.797
- Oh, my God.
Where have you been?

16:12.841 --> 16:14.234
I've been trying
to call you all day.

16:14.277 --> 16:15.539
- Sorry.

16:15.583 --> 16:17.019
Harry gave me the day off,

16:17.063 --> 16:19.456
so I ditched my phone,
and I hiked the mountain loop,

16:19.500 --> 16:21.719
and now I've come in
to spread the joy.

16:21.763 --> 16:23.939
- Yeah!
[both groan]

16:23.983 --> 16:25.158
- What's new with you?

16:25.201 --> 16:27.203
- Besides the date last night.

16:27.247 --> 16:29.118
- Date? With who?

16:29.162 --> 16:31.599
[gasps]
Hot baseball guy?

16:31.642 --> 16:33.253
- Um, braindead, yeah.

16:33.296 --> 16:36.604
We talked about it yesterday,
like, literally right here.

16:36.647 --> 16:38.780
- Really?
Okay, I'm sorry.

16:38.823 --> 16:41.957
I spaced or something.
How'd it go?

16:42.001 --> 16:43.959
- He might be pretty great.
I don't know.

16:44.003 --> 16:46.048
Ah, ah.
- Oh!

16:46.092 --> 16:48.398
Stop it. It was the best date.

16:48.442 --> 16:50.400
- Yeah, I'll let him
take me out again.

16:50.444 --> 16:52.881
- Yeah, see? So stop it.

16:52.924 --> 16:55.971
Stop being insecure.
You're amazing.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.668
And you're gonna go out
with him again.

16:57.712 --> 16:59.148
Ah, I don't know why.

16:59.192 --> 17:00.976
I just have a really good
feeling about this.

17:01.020 --> 17:03.065
- You're smiling so big,
it's kind of creeping me out.

17:03.109 --> 17:04.458
- [laughs]

17:04.501 --> 17:06.155
[gunshot]

17:06.199 --> 17:10.420
[eerie music]

17:10.464 --> 17:12.074
- Ah!
- Oh!

17:12.118 --> 17:13.641
- You okay?

17:13.684 --> 17:18.037
That's just Judy
and Judy's Judy playing pool.

17:18.080 --> 17:19.647
- Uh, yeah.
I--

17:19.690 --> 17:22.824
[chuckles]
No, I'm fine.

17:22.867 --> 17:26.828
I think I'm just tired
from the hike.

17:26.871 --> 17:28.569
- Couple out-of-towners
rented the boat

17:28.612 --> 17:30.179
three days ago, paid cash.

17:30.223 --> 17:31.398
Someone found it this morning

17:31.441 --> 17:32.703
floating on the other side
of the lake.

17:32.747 --> 17:34.270
- You have any idea
where they was from?

17:34.314 --> 17:35.663
- I don't know.

17:35.706 --> 17:38.100
Fake accents, gold chains.
Maybe New York.

17:38.144 --> 17:42.017
- Manhattan, or Long island?
New Jersey?

17:42.061 --> 17:44.672
Like, "Hey, Joey,

17:44.715 --> 17:46.674
Let's head down the shore
and rent a boat."

17:46.717 --> 17:48.241
You know,
just a couple shoobies

17:48.284 --> 17:51.113
chowin' hoagies, floatin',
listening to the Boss.

17:51.157 --> 17:52.332
- What are you doing?

17:52.375 --> 17:54.116
- I'm trying
to pinpoint them, sir.

17:54.160 --> 17:55.204
- Please don't, all right?

17:55.248 --> 17:56.684
It's making
a very uncomfortable.

17:56.727 --> 17:58.947
- New Jersey
sounds about right.

17:58.990 --> 18:00.514
- New Jersey.

18:01.906 --> 18:04.735
- Is there a reason
you didn't call me?

18:04.779 --> 18:07.129
- I'm sorry.
We lab partners now?

18:07.173 --> 18:11.220
Now I'm supposed to fill you
in on all my cases?

18:11.264 --> 18:12.874
- See that van over there?

18:12.917 --> 18:14.484
Matches the description
of the vehicle

18:14.528 --> 18:16.356
the victim entered
the night he was killed.

18:16.399 --> 18:19.576
New Jersey plates, partner.

18:22.144 --> 18:23.798
- New Jersey.

18:31.110 --> 18:33.721
- Hey, Jay. How are you?

18:33.764 --> 18:35.114
- You couldn't do it,
could you?

18:35.157 --> 18:36.593
- What?

18:36.637 --> 18:37.551
- Do you think it was easy
for me to ask you

18:37.594 --> 18:38.900
to take me out for my birthday?

18:38.943 --> 18:41.990
- Whoa, birthday?
What are you talking about?

18:42.033 --> 18:43.731
- God, I figured that might be
the one thing

18:43.774 --> 18:45.254
that mattered to you.

18:45.298 --> 18:46.429
I waited outside the diner

18:46.473 --> 18:47.909
for two hours
for you to pick me up.

18:47.952 --> 18:49.519
- Okay, slow down.
I don't understand.

18:49.563 --> 18:51.478
When did you ask me
to take you out?

18:51.521 --> 18:54.350
- Harry's party.
Are you kidding me right now?

18:54.394 --> 18:57.179
- No. Jay, wait.

18:57.223 --> 18:58.485
Jay!

18:58.528 --> 19:01.357
[solemn music]

19:01.401 --> 19:03.098
Harry.

19:03.142 --> 19:06.580
♪

19:06.623 --> 19:08.582
What did you do?

19:08.625 --> 19:11.585
- I only glued the yogurt
to the shelf

19:11.628 --> 19:13.717
because someone
keeps stealing it.

19:15.589 --> 19:17.286
- You erased my memory,
didn't you?

19:17.330 --> 19:19.114
[suspenseful music]

19:19.158 --> 19:20.594
Why?

19:20.637 --> 19:22.770
- You asked me to.

19:22.813 --> 19:26.121
- Jay asked me to take her out
for her birthday.

19:26.165 --> 19:31.082
Me, Harry, and you erased it.
Why would you do that?

19:31.126 --> 19:33.172
- I did it for you.

19:34.999 --> 19:40.614
You were sad.
You wanted me to take it away.

19:40.657 --> 19:43.182
- What happened?
Why was I sad?

19:44.966 --> 19:46.228
- Are you gonna write back?
- No.

19:46.272 --> 19:48.796
I mean, in a couple days.
What am I, desperate?

19:48.839 --> 19:50.276
- You're ridiculous.
Text him back.

19:50.319 --> 19:51.799
[gunshot]

19:51.842 --> 19:54.193
- God, who's that?
- Stay right here.

19:56.978 --> 19:59.763
- You should have just stayed
in Colorado and done your job.

19:59.807 --> 20:02.157
- You shot me.
- Yeah.

20:02.201 --> 20:04.507
Like you shot
two of my guys in New York.

20:04.551 --> 20:07.293
I should have never made you
kill Sam Hodges.

20:07.336 --> 20:10.034
I should have
just taken care of it myself.

20:10.078 --> 20:11.253
[gunshot]

20:11.297 --> 20:17.912
♪

20:19.609 --> 20:22.569
- I killed him.

20:22.612 --> 20:25.659
- You did it to save me.

20:25.702 --> 20:29.315
- But I killed...

20:29.358 --> 20:32.056
a human being.

20:34.189 --> 20:36.670
- This is why
I erased your memory.

20:40.151 --> 20:43.242
[suspenseful music]

20:43.285 --> 20:44.895
[elevator dings]

20:44.939 --> 20:47.463
- Ooh, be careful
of your case files, sir.

20:47.507 --> 20:50.161
That crime scavenger is here.

20:50.205 --> 20:52.773
- Well, I'd be more worried
about your sandwich.

20:52.816 --> 20:54.122
She might swoop down
from her perch

20:54.165 --> 20:55.558
and fly away with your ham.

20:55.602 --> 20:57.691
[both laugh]

20:57.734 --> 20:59.345
- Good to see
you're not letting murder

20:59.388 --> 21:00.781
keep the laughter away.

21:00.824 --> 21:01.999
- Yeah, well it's not
the deputy's fault.

21:02.043 --> 21:03.305
She finds me hysterical.

21:03.349 --> 21:05.394
Every time I open up my mouth,
she laughs.

21:07.178 --> 21:08.092
- [laughs]

21:10.051 --> 21:12.358
- We're on our way
to tracking down

21:12.401 --> 21:13.794
the men from the van.

21:13.837 --> 21:16.753
The deputy's on hold
with the NYPD.

21:16.797 --> 21:19.452
- Vincent Grillo
and Joey Moretti.

21:19.495 --> 21:21.976
Both served time.
Both have ties to the mob.

21:22.019 --> 21:25.284
Suspects in several hits.
You name it, they've done it.

21:26.981 --> 21:28.417
- How'd you ID them so quick?

21:28.461 --> 21:30.027
- Caught the driver
on a security camera,

21:30.071 --> 21:31.594
pulled a partial print
from the dash,

21:31.638 --> 21:33.988
and then I called up
some favors

21:34.031 --> 21:36.338
at my old stomping ground
at the NYPD.

21:36.382 --> 21:39.602
- Well, well, New York cop.
You didn't mention.

21:39.646 --> 21:41.691
D.C. myself, 11 years.

21:41.735 --> 21:43.563
- Huh. Look at us.

21:43.606 --> 21:46.261
A couple big city cops
playing in a tiny town.

21:46.305 --> 21:50.657
- Oops, better keep an eye
on my sandwich.

21:50.700 --> 21:51.919
- You know this guy
I grew up with

21:51.962 --> 21:55.879
is a New York cop.
Do you know Luis Valez?

21:55.923 --> 21:57.490
- I haven't heard
that name for years.

21:57.533 --> 21:59.535
Luis was my trainer
at the academy.

21:59.579 --> 22:00.797
- [laughs]
Stop it.

22:00.841 --> 22:02.364
You heard that, Deputy?
She know Luis.

22:02.408 --> 22:07.500
- Sorry, just checking
to see if my ham is gone.

22:07.543 --> 22:09.893
- Look, Sheriff,

22:09.937 --> 22:11.982
I know you're not happy
about sharing this case.

22:12.026 --> 22:15.072
- Hmm.
- But together we can crack it.

22:15.116 --> 22:16.770
- You know what?
I believe we can.

22:16.813 --> 22:18.728
You know, bring a little
big city perspective

22:18.772 --> 22:20.774
to this small town tomfoolery.

22:20.817 --> 22:22.428
- Caw, caw.

22:25.082 --> 22:29.870
Sorry, just thought
I saw a bird in here.

22:29.913 --> 22:36.659
♪

22:36.703 --> 22:40.794
- I gave you your memory back.
Why are you angry with me?

22:40.837 --> 22:43.753
Killing that man
was a good thing.

22:43.797 --> 22:46.060
We are now both the same.

22:46.103 --> 22:49.585
We are both murderers.
We should start a club.

22:49.629 --> 22:54.416
- You can't just go around
erasing people's memories.

22:54.460 --> 22:58.594
- You wanted me to it
when the sheriff and the deputy

22:58.638 --> 23:00.509
found out what I am.

23:00.553 --> 23:02.381
- The fate of the world
depended on that,

23:02.424 --> 23:04.295
so I think
that one was important.

23:04.339 --> 23:06.820
- I think erasing your memory
was important.

23:06.863 --> 23:10.084
I do not like it
when you are upset.

23:10.127 --> 23:12.695
You get loud and blubbery.

23:12.739 --> 23:14.001
- Yes, I was upset,

23:14.044 --> 23:16.177
but that was my grief
to deal with, not yours.

23:16.220 --> 23:18.701
- The second I got rid of it,
you were happy.

23:18.745 --> 23:21.138
You smiled.
I saw your teeth.

23:21.182 --> 23:23.489
I didn't even know
you had teeth.

23:23.532 --> 23:24.925
- Listen to me.

23:24.968 --> 23:27.971
Life is not just about
smiling and happiness.

23:28.015 --> 23:30.452
It's also about pain

23:30.496 --> 23:33.324
and guilt and fear.

23:33.368 --> 23:36.153
They're called feelings
for a reason so you feel them.

23:36.197 --> 23:37.851
- Those are bad feelings.

23:37.894 --> 23:39.461
When I feel bad feelings,

23:39.505 --> 23:43.813
I think about season five
of "Law & Order."

23:43.857 --> 23:46.773
[soft sentimental music]

23:46.816 --> 23:48.078
♪

23:48.122 --> 23:49.732
I'm happy now.
I'm thinking about it now.

23:49.776 --> 23:52.039
I'm happy.
- Really?

23:52.082 --> 23:53.170
You're not freaked out at all

23:53.214 --> 23:55.303
that you almost died
that night?

23:55.346 --> 23:58.480
- I did--I did not almost die.

23:58.524 --> 24:00.830
I'm gonna put in the DVD
and watch it now.

24:00.874 --> 24:03.093
- No, I remember.
I saw your eyes.

24:03.137 --> 24:05.487
You are in denial, Harry.
You could have died.

24:05.531 --> 24:07.010
You were scared.

24:07.054 --> 24:09.404
- Season five
of "Law & Order,"

24:09.448 --> 24:13.539
they introduce Assistant
District Attorney Jack McCoy.

24:13.582 --> 24:16.846
I like Jack McCoy.
Let's watch it together.

24:16.890 --> 24:21.111
- What you're doing is called
burying your feelings.

24:21.155 --> 24:24.375
All humans do it.

24:24.419 --> 24:26.203
You might not want to deal
with your feelings,

24:26.247 --> 24:27.944
but I plan
on dealing with mine,

24:27.988 --> 24:32.645
so please, please
stay out of my head.

24:36.170 --> 24:39.478
- I will watch season five
by myself.

24:39.521 --> 24:44.483
♪

24:51.185 --> 24:54.101
[eerie music]

24:54.144 --> 24:57.278
[dog growling]

25:01.282 --> 25:04.633
- Bobby?
Bobby, is that you?

25:04.677 --> 25:08.071
- Grandma, Bobby went missing
80 years ago.

25:08.115 --> 25:10.552
- I know my own brother.

25:10.596 --> 25:12.685
- [hisses]

25:12.728 --> 25:13.860
[hisses]

25:13.903 --> 25:19.082
♪

25:19.126 --> 25:21.084
- It's the alien baby.

25:21.128 --> 25:24.044
[dog barking]

25:26.786 --> 25:29.353
- So this is it?

25:29.397 --> 25:31.965
- Oh, is this where I find out
you're a serial killer?

25:32.008 --> 25:34.489
- I'm more of an oatmeal guy.
- Mm.

25:34.533 --> 25:36.970
- Get it?
Cause it's cereal--

25:37.013 --> 25:39.233
- No, no, I got it.

25:39.276 --> 25:40.887
Yeah, I'm just surprised
you said it.

25:40.930 --> 25:42.976
[both chuckle]

25:43.019 --> 25:45.065
- So when they expanded
the building site,

25:45.108 --> 25:46.980
they found native artifacts.

25:47.023 --> 25:48.547
My agency was brought in

25:48.590 --> 25:51.027
to preserve and catalog
what we find.

25:53.769 --> 25:55.423
- What's with the backhoe?

25:55.466 --> 25:57.860
- Oh, that--
that's this whole dance

25:57.904 --> 26:00.820
we're doing with the contractor
who's pissed we're here,

26:00.863 --> 26:05.302
and he parks it there
so we don't expand the dig.

26:05.346 --> 26:09.306
- Cool, so he's an asshole.
- [chuckles]

26:09.350 --> 26:13.136
- Take a look at this--
broken pottery,

26:13.180 --> 26:17.967
usually a good bet
we're on or near a village.

26:18.011 --> 26:21.231
Found a fire pit
and some flint for tools.

26:21.275 --> 26:23.407
I pretty much guarantee
we'd find some foundations

26:23.451 --> 26:27.150
for huts
underneath that backhoe.

26:27.194 --> 26:29.283
- Wow, did you really get

26:29.326 --> 26:33.156
into all this
because of "Indiana Jones"?

26:33.200 --> 26:35.942
- That was more for wordplay.
- Mm.

26:35.985 --> 26:38.466
- Yeah, I wasn't
raised traditionally.

26:38.509 --> 26:41.034
For my tribe,
a lot of the old ways died

26:41.077 --> 26:42.688
with my
grandmother's generation

26:42.731 --> 26:45.473
in the boarding schools.

26:45.516 --> 26:47.606
- Oh, sorry.

26:49.433 --> 26:52.480
- There's something
about being down in the dirt,

26:52.523 --> 26:57.180
holding the artifacts,
the physicality of it.

26:57.224 --> 26:58.747
I feel like I'm connected

26:58.791 --> 27:00.967
to something
I thought was gone forever.

27:01.010 --> 27:03.970
[tender music]

27:04.013 --> 27:06.494
- I think it's incredible

27:06.537 --> 27:11.499
that you're doing something
important with your life.

27:11.542 --> 27:15.416
I usually just push booze
and get people wasted.

27:15.459 --> 27:18.506
That's me.

27:18.549 --> 27:20.987
- You can do anything.
- Yeah.

27:21.030 --> 27:22.379
I used to think that way,

27:22.423 --> 27:25.339
but after my accident,
not so much.

27:25.382 --> 27:27.994
- Well, we are who we are
because of our history,

27:28.037 --> 27:30.649
not in spite of it.

27:30.692 --> 27:32.302
It doesn't make it right.

27:32.346 --> 27:33.956
Doesn't mean
we're stuck, either.

27:34.000 --> 27:39.483
♪

27:39.527 --> 27:42.704
Now, where are you going?
- Getting you unstuck.

27:42.748 --> 27:46.447
[Wyatt C. Louis's
"Dancing with Sue"]

27:46.490 --> 27:47.753
- You sure this is a good idea?

27:47.796 --> 27:50.451
[engine rumbles]

27:50.494 --> 27:53.846
[upbeat country music]

27:53.889 --> 27:57.327
- ♪ Follow me here,
follow me there ♪

27:57.371 --> 28:00.374
♪ Spin you around
in that red dress ♪

28:00.417 --> 28:04.030
♪ I found for you
at a thrift store ♪

28:04.073 --> 28:07.163
♪ Just down the street
from our first house ♪

28:07.207 --> 28:13.343
♪

28:13.387 --> 28:15.911
♪ Getting down with the sun

28:15.955 --> 28:21.090
♪ I need you right now

28:21.134 --> 28:22.265
- That was probably

28:22.309 --> 28:23.702
the hottest thing
I've ever seen.

28:23.745 --> 28:25.225
- Well, what can I say,
you know?

28:25.268 --> 28:26.792
You needed something moved,

28:26.835 --> 28:30.447
and I'm just a lady who knows
how to drive a backhoe.

28:30.491 --> 28:32.232
- I think I can work with that.

28:32.275 --> 28:39.195
♪

28:39.674 --> 28:42.721
- I wanna talk to you
about something.

28:42.764 --> 28:45.724
Um, yeah, I just...

28:48.727 --> 28:51.207
Uh...

28:51.251 --> 28:54.254
sorry, it's hard.
Uh, hmm.

28:54.297 --> 28:56.778
- Are you afraid
to tell me something?

28:58.824 --> 29:01.783
- Well, I think I'm, uh...

29:01.827 --> 29:06.135
I think maybe I'm afraid
to tell you anything.

29:08.616 --> 29:09.748
- Wow.

29:11.314 --> 29:14.448
That's horrible.

29:14.491 --> 29:16.711
Do you understand
how that makes me feel?

29:16.755 --> 29:18.844
- Mm-hmm.

29:18.887 --> 29:20.802
- Wait, is that--

29:20.846 --> 29:22.325
is that why
you wanted to come here?

29:22.369 --> 29:23.936
So you would have
some public protection?

29:23.979 --> 29:25.764
- [chuckles]
No.

29:28.201 --> 29:30.507
Yes, I--

29:32.858 --> 29:35.338
- That's great.

29:35.382 --> 29:37.732
- Look, it's not just you.
You know me.

29:37.776 --> 29:42.824
I'm afraid of everything,
and you're technically a thing

29:42.868 --> 29:45.479
that I love very much.

29:45.522 --> 29:49.222
- I just can't believe
that you're--you're what?

29:49.265 --> 29:50.919
You're afraid of me?

29:50.963 --> 29:54.270
- Oh, no, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean it like that.

29:54.314 --> 29:56.490
- You did.

29:56.533 --> 29:57.752
It's probably
the most honest thing

29:57.796 --> 29:59.710
you've said to me
in a long time.

30:04.019 --> 30:05.064
You know what?

30:05.107 --> 30:08.154
Um, I am not hungry anymore,

30:08.197 --> 30:10.547
so I think I'm just gonna
meet you at home.

30:18.860 --> 30:22.124
- Well, at least there was
no one here to see that.

30:22.168 --> 30:23.865
- I saw it.

30:27.695 --> 30:30.089
- Do you recognize
either one of these men?

30:30.132 --> 30:31.525
- Yeah, that's them.

30:31.568 --> 30:33.222
The guy with the big head
and the guy with the head.

30:33.266 --> 30:35.355
- They were the ones
in the van?

30:35.398 --> 30:38.358
- Um, can you not?
I'm talking to Mike.

30:38.401 --> 30:40.882
So was there anything else

30:40.926 --> 30:44.581
that you wanted
to ask me about, Mikey?

30:44.625 --> 30:47.323
- Uh, were they the men
you saw in the van?

30:47.367 --> 30:49.195
- Yes, they were.

30:49.238 --> 30:53.155
Yes, I can comply
with that information.

30:53.199 --> 30:56.115
- Wow, Chinese food.
Good timing.

30:56.158 --> 30:59.292
I was just gonna see if there
was any cheese in the fridge.

30:59.335 --> 31:00.728
- Yeah, Lena I brought it in
from Jessup.

31:00.771 --> 31:03.557
It's actually pretty amazing.
- How nice of her.

31:03.600 --> 31:05.124
- Best Chinese food
west of New York City.

31:05.167 --> 31:06.473
- Oh, wait a minute.

31:06.516 --> 31:09.215
D.C. is west of New York City.
- Oh, hell no.

31:09.258 --> 31:10.259
Don't even try comparing

31:10.303 --> 31:12.609
D.C. Chinese food
with New York.

31:12.653 --> 31:14.394
- Any chance you cut this

31:14.437 --> 31:18.702
in half with a knife,
or are these teeth marks?

31:18.746 --> 31:20.574
- She just ID'd
the two guys in the van,

31:20.617 --> 31:22.489
so I'm gonna go call my team
and fill 'em in.

31:22.532 --> 31:23.925
Ah, thank you.

31:27.581 --> 31:30.410
- Seems like there's
not a lot of food left here.

31:30.453 --> 31:32.107
- Oh, you can have
my cookie, Liv.

31:32.151 --> 31:33.761
I just want the fortune part.

31:36.111 --> 31:37.852
- Thanks.

31:37.896 --> 31:41.856
- Ooh, "You will soon
meet your lover."

31:41.900 --> 31:45.599
Oh, my God, Mike, look.
It's like boom.

31:45.642 --> 31:47.340
- Looks like
we're headed to Jessup.

31:47.383 --> 31:49.298
My team
just found medical records

31:49.342 --> 31:50.996
stashed in the trunk
of the victim's vehicle.

31:51.039 --> 31:53.563
They belong to Sam Hodges.

31:53.607 --> 31:56.610
[William Elliott Whitmore's
"Johnny Law"]

31:56.653 --> 32:00.788
[lively acoustic guitar music]

32:00.831 --> 32:04.009
- ♪ Oh, Johnny Law

32:04.052 --> 32:06.098
- I think this may be
the smoking gun we need.

32:06.141 --> 32:09.971
- ♪ Well, you're the
littlest man I ever saw ♪

32:10.015 --> 32:12.495
♪ With your badge
and your gun ♪

32:12.539 --> 32:15.107
♪ You just hassle everyone

32:15.150 --> 32:18.980
♪ He'll get you on the run,
Johnny Law ♪

32:28.337 --> 32:31.950
- I got you
your chef's salad to go.

32:36.041 --> 32:37.390
[sighs]

32:37.433 --> 32:39.827
Honey, I...

32:39.870 --> 32:42.699
I didn't mean to say
that I was afraid of you.

32:44.179 --> 32:45.702
Please don't be mad.

32:47.139 --> 32:51.970
- Actually, I'm not.
It's not just you.

32:54.624 --> 32:56.887
There are things
you should have told me...

32:58.498 --> 33:00.935
But I also know that
I don't make it easy

33:00.979 --> 33:02.415
for you
to talk to me sometimes.

33:02.458 --> 33:04.678
[tender music]

33:04.721 --> 33:07.550
I never used to be this way.

33:07.594 --> 33:09.683
- Me neither.

33:09.726 --> 33:13.774
I mean...
[sighs]

33:13.817 --> 33:15.297
Remember when we first met

33:15.341 --> 33:19.171
and we could talk on the phone
forever about nothing?

33:19.214 --> 33:20.563
- I know.

33:22.391 --> 33:27.527
But we've been together
a long time.

33:27.570 --> 33:28.745
Things change.

33:30.791 --> 33:34.621
I love you,
and I know that you love me.

33:36.144 --> 33:38.538
We've got a wonderful kid
and a good life

33:38.581 --> 33:40.409
with a new baby on the way.

33:40.453 --> 33:42.455
Maybe this is
just what we are now.

33:42.498 --> 33:48.765
♪

33:48.809 --> 33:51.072
Thanks for this.
- Sure.

33:59.689 --> 34:02.779
[phone ringing]

34:09.482 --> 34:10.570
- Hello?

34:10.613 --> 34:13.094
- Hey, what's up?

34:13.138 --> 34:16.967
- Uh, nothing.
I'm in the kitchen.

34:17.011 --> 34:18.230
- Cool, cool.

34:18.273 --> 34:20.101
What's the--
what's the weather like there?

34:20.145 --> 34:21.668
- What are you doing?

34:21.711 --> 34:24.279
- You know,
just haven't been able

34:24.323 --> 34:26.064
to stop thinking about you

34:26.107 --> 34:29.763
ever since I saw you
in the living room.

34:29.806 --> 34:32.418
[Warren Zevon's
"Don't Let Us Get Sick"]

34:32.461 --> 34:35.116
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

34:35.160 --> 34:39.686
Just wondering if you're
a dog person or a cat person.

34:39.729 --> 34:41.514
[soft guitar music]

34:41.557 --> 34:44.604
- I actually really like mice.
- Really?

34:44.647 --> 34:46.214
[both chuckle]

34:46.258 --> 34:47.824
- Well, just like you can tell
a lot about a person based on

34:47.868 --> 34:49.391
who their favorite Beatle is.

34:49.435 --> 34:51.480
- Okay, let's see.
John Lennon.

34:51.524 --> 34:52.786
- Hm, that's obvious.

34:52.829 --> 34:54.004
You play the guitar,

34:54.048 --> 34:56.181
and you smoke
a lot of 1960s hash.

34:56.224 --> 34:57.617
- What's hash?

34:57.660 --> 35:00.185
- To m--from what I've read,

35:00.228 --> 35:03.579
it's a mixture of armpit hair
and dryer lint.

35:03.623 --> 35:05.146
- Sometimes I have this dream

35:05.190 --> 35:08.193
where I'm falling out
of an airplane,

35:08.236 --> 35:10.499
and on the way down,
all I can think is,

35:10.543 --> 35:13.154
"I'm not gonna get
mileage points for this."

35:13.198 --> 35:17.071
- ♪ Don't let us get stupid,
all right? ♪

35:17.115 --> 35:19.987
♪ Just make us be brave

35:20.030 --> 35:21.467
- Do you know we've been
on the phone

35:21.510 --> 35:23.556
for, like, three hours?

35:23.599 --> 35:25.427
- It's felt like five minutes.

35:25.471 --> 35:28.648
♪

35:28.691 --> 35:31.825
I must be falling
in love with you.

35:31.868 --> 35:38.005
I hope that doesn't,
you know, scare you away.

35:38.048 --> 35:40.921
- No, it doesn't.

35:40.964 --> 35:42.923
- What time is it
where you are?

35:42.966 --> 35:45.752
- [laughs]

35:45.795 --> 35:52.846
♪

35:52.889 --> 35:55.196
- ♪ The moon has a face

35:55.240 --> 35:58.373
♪ And it smiles on the lake

35:58.417 --> 36:02.334
♪ And causes the ripples
in time ♪

36:02.377 --> 36:04.423
♪

36:04.466 --> 36:06.642
♪ I'm lucky to be here

36:06.686 --> 36:09.384
♪ With someone I like

36:09.428 --> 36:13.388
♪ Who maketh my spirit
to shine ♪

36:13.432 --> 36:15.173
♪

36:15.216 --> 36:17.697
♪ Don't let us get sick

36:17.740 --> 36:20.526
♪ Don't let us get old

36:20.569 --> 36:24.399
♪ Don't let us get stupid,
all right? ♪

36:24.443 --> 36:26.096
♪

36:26.140 --> 36:28.882
♪ Just make us be brave

36:28.925 --> 36:31.928
♪ And make us play nice

36:31.972 --> 36:35.715
♪ And let us
be together tonight ♪

36:35.758 --> 36:37.064
♪

36:37.107 --> 36:39.762
♪ Don't let us get sick

36:39.806 --> 36:42.548
♪ Don't let us get old

36:42.591 --> 36:46.769
♪ Don't let us get stupid,
all right? ♪

36:46.813 --> 36:48.510
♪

36:48.554 --> 36:51.600
♪ Just make us be brave

36:51.644 --> 36:53.950
♪ And make us play nice

36:53.994 --> 36:57.215
♪ And let us
be together tonight ♪

37:00.566 --> 37:03.482
[suspenseful music]

37:03.525 --> 37:05.484
♪

37:05.527 --> 37:06.789
- Where have you been?

37:06.833 --> 37:09.227
I've been calling you
on your walkie talkie.

37:09.270 --> 37:13.013
- I lost it.
- It's right there.

37:13.056 --> 37:14.406
- Wow, thank you
for finding it.

37:14.449 --> 37:16.799
- Why does the RV
smell like dirt?

37:16.843 --> 37:20.238
And why are there
extra feet in here?

37:20.281 --> 37:22.675
- Look, I didn't wanna
show you this,

37:22.718 --> 37:24.111
but now I have no choice.

37:26.069 --> 37:30.465
Eighty years ago,
a boy went missing in Patience.

37:30.509 --> 37:33.599
I found him.

37:33.642 --> 37:35.165
- You found a zombie?

37:35.209 --> 37:37.690
That's dangerous,
Zombies eat brains.

37:37.733 --> 37:40.910
- That's not dangerous for you.
And it's not a zombie.

37:42.695 --> 37:44.305
- An alien!

37:44.349 --> 37:46.960
- The alien baby must have
found Bobby Smallwood's remains

37:47.003 --> 37:49.397
and used the DNA
to take over his body.

37:53.314 --> 37:56.186
Bad baby!
- [grunts]

37:56.230 --> 37:59.581
- Where are your manners?
- [hisses]

37:59.625 --> 38:01.801
- Why didn't you tell me
you found the alien?

38:01.844 --> 38:03.498
- Because you're
Harry's puppet,

38:03.542 --> 38:05.283
and he can't know
we have the baby.

38:05.326 --> 38:09.939
- Hey, Harry's my puppet,
and I won't say anything.

38:09.983 --> 38:12.072
I don't talk to puppets.
- Good.

38:12.115 --> 38:14.248
Because Harry is breeding
these things to be evil,

38:14.292 --> 38:16.119
but I'm going to thwart
his plan

38:16.163 --> 38:19.166
by teaching baby here
to be good.

38:21.255 --> 38:24.737
Baby, I told you
not to eat your toys!

38:24.780 --> 38:26.086
- [hisses]

38:26.129 --> 38:30.395
♪

38:36.052 --> 38:37.402
- What did you do?

38:37.445 --> 38:40.187
Did you order all
the comfort food on the menu?

38:40.230 --> 38:42.798
My dad is afraid
your heart is gonna explode.

38:42.842 --> 38:47.150
- I asked them to fry the pie,
but they wouldn't do it!

38:47.194 --> 38:49.196
- You know what
you're doing here, right?

38:50.763 --> 38:53.635
You were shot.
You're scared and confused.

38:53.679 --> 38:55.942
And now you're using food
to make yourself feel better.

38:55.985 --> 38:59.815
- Yes, I am. It works.

38:59.859 --> 39:02.383
Humans should do it.

39:02.427 --> 39:03.645
- They do.

39:05.386 --> 39:07.083
- I'm sorry I erased
your memory

39:07.127 --> 39:09.129
and ruined your lunch with Jay.

39:10.565 --> 39:14.221
I should have let you feel
your own pain.

39:14.264 --> 39:16.745
- Life is hard...

39:16.789 --> 39:20.270
which is why we have to deal
with the hard stuff,

39:20.314 --> 39:23.491
like the alien baby
I now remember is on the loose.

39:25.101 --> 39:27.626
- I need more fries!
- No.

39:27.669 --> 39:31.020
No more fries until you admit
you're afraid to die.

39:31.064 --> 39:33.893
- Are you afraid to die?

39:33.936 --> 39:35.808
- Death is complicated.

39:35.851 --> 39:39.551
That's why people
don't really think about it.

39:39.594 --> 39:42.249
Or they eat through
their emotions.

39:42.292 --> 39:45.426
- See, I'm normal. Hmm?

39:45.470 --> 39:49.996
- No, everyone is going
to die someday, and it's scary.

39:50.039 --> 39:52.390
I know that I'm gonna die,
but if I spend every second

39:52.433 --> 39:55.175
worrying about it,
then I can't live.

39:55.218 --> 39:57.525
And part of the living
is feeling it all.

39:57.569 --> 40:01.268
The good lifts you up,
and the bad knocks you down,

40:01.311 --> 40:05.359
but you need the bad.
You need those hard times.

40:05.403 --> 40:08.057
If I can get past
the bad stuff--

40:08.101 --> 40:09.842
missing Jay's birthday...

40:09.885 --> 40:11.713
[soft sentimental music]

40:11.757 --> 40:14.542
My mom leaving me behind,

40:14.586 --> 40:19.242
the guy trying to kill you--
it will make me stronger.

40:21.506 --> 40:23.551
Everyone has their own
relationship with death.

40:25.640 --> 40:27.076
That's mine.

40:28.556 --> 40:30.732
You have to figure out yours.

40:30.776 --> 40:32.255
- [grumbles softly]

40:33.822 --> 40:38.218
- Every--every morning,
Elaine would wake early

40:38.261 --> 40:42.265
and have tea ready for me
before I went to work.

40:42.309 --> 40:44.790
I'm glad she's gone.

40:44.833 --> 40:49.142
She'd hate having to see me

40:49.185 --> 40:50.622
in such pain.

40:50.665 --> 40:53.886
- You will not be
in any pain soon,

40:53.929 --> 40:55.757
when you are dead.

40:55.801 --> 40:58.543
- It will be nice
to see my wife again.

40:58.586 --> 41:01.415
- Will she be waiting
for you in hell?

41:01.459 --> 41:05.680
- [laughs]
No, I hope in heaven.

41:05.724 --> 41:09.423
- Oh, I get
your fairy tales mixed up.

41:11.338 --> 41:12.600
I am afraid of death.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.255
- Oh, you--you--
you shouldn't be.

41:15.298 --> 41:19.477
- How are you not afraid?
You will be dead soon.

41:21.087 --> 41:22.436
- Oh, no.

41:22.480 --> 41:25.047
The things got better
when I found out

41:25.091 --> 41:27.702
that I was dying.
[chuckles]

41:27.746 --> 41:33.447
It reminded me
that life isn't forever.

41:33.491 --> 41:38.365
I-I began to appreciate
every moment.

41:38.408 --> 41:42.500
- Like when there is only
one slice of pie left...

41:44.240 --> 41:46.155
It tastes better.

41:46.199 --> 41:49.115
- Exactly.
[chuckles]

41:49.158 --> 41:52.118
[tender music]

41:52.161 --> 41:54.468
♪

41:54.512 --> 41:59.168
Thank you for--
for doing this for me.

42:01.649 --> 42:06.175
- My friend told me I should
not run away from death.

42:09.918 --> 42:13.835
Killing you...

42:13.879 --> 42:16.185
is not running away.

42:21.495 --> 42:23.932
- Thank you, Harry.

42:26.282 --> 42:27.849
- Goodbye, Gerard.

42:27.893 --> 42:34.856
♪

42:41.254 --> 42:42.821
- [whispers]
What is it like?

42:42.864 --> 42:44.997
[Olivier Andrès and Eric
Boroian's "My Heart Falls"]

42:45.040 --> 42:46.694
- How can it be 18 years

42:46.738 --> 42:50.611
since I held your little body
close to mine?

42:50.655 --> 42:52.178
I'm so sorry
for the way you found out

42:52.221 --> 42:54.528
I was your mother,

42:54.572 --> 42:58.097
but I'm also grateful
that it happened

42:58.140 --> 43:04.669
no matter how hard it was
because now you know.

43:04.712 --> 43:07.367
And sometimes
the hardest things in life

43:07.410 --> 43:10.413
create light and hope

43:10.457 --> 43:13.982
and take you
one step closer to happiness.

43:14.026 --> 43:16.855
- ♪ Through my heart

43:16.898 --> 43:20.946
- Happy birthday,
my beautiful Jay.

43:20.989 --> 43:25.472
- ♪ And my heart falls,
falls ♪

43:25.515 --> 43:27.387
- I love you
more than anything.

43:27.430 --> 43:31.913
- ♪ And my heart falls

43:31.957 --> 43:34.829
- Your mom.

43:34.873 --> 43:38.224
♪

43:38.267 --> 43:41.531
- ♪ Who

43:41.575 --> 43:45.144
♪ Hey, hey

43:45.187 --> 43:48.451
♪ You hold my heart

43:48.495 --> 43:49.975
♪

43:50.018 --> 43:52.804
♪ Don't you?
